	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">HEBREW CONGREGATION</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">OF</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#8220;THE DISPERSED OF JUDAH.&#8221;</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;</p>
				<p>SIR&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You are hereby notified that the sale of the seats of the Synagogue of this Congregation&#44; will take place<lb/> at the Synagogue on <date>Sunday next&#44; the 29th</date> instant&#44; at 10 o&#39;clock&#44; A. M.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The following are extracts from the minutes of the Board of Officers in relation to the sale of the Seats.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The seats are rated as follows&#58;</p>
				<p>ALL THE GENTLEMEN&#39;S First row or front seats each &#45; &#45; 812.00 per annum.</p>
				<p>&#8220;&#8220;&#8220;          Second &#8220;      &#8220;   &#8220;    &#45; &#45;     8.00 &#8220;        &#8220;</p>
				<p>&#8220;&#8220;&#8220;                    Third    &#8220;      &#8220;       &#8220;    &#45; &#45;     5.00 &#8220;        &#8220;</p>
				<p>&#8220;          &#8220;LADIES&#39;       First row or front seats each &#45; &#45;    10.00 &#8220;&#8220;</p>
				<p>&#8220;&#8220;&#8220;          Second &#8220;                 &#8220;  &#8220;     &#45; &#45;      7.50 &#8220;&#8220;</p>
				<p>&#8220;&#8220;&#8220;          Third    &#8220;      &#8220;  &#8220;     &#45; &#45;      4.00 &#8220;&#8220;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The choice of one&#44; with the privilege of the remaining seats on the same bench between arms&#44; shall be sold<lb/> for the term of two years from the <date>29th</date> instant.  Rent to be paid monthly&#58; Pre&#45;emption money&#44; to be paid at the time<lb/> of sale for the first year&#44; and the same pre&#45;emption at the commencement of the second year.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The sale of all seats is thrown open at the above assessed rates&#44; and possession given on <date>Friday&#44; the 3d<lb/> April</date> next&#59; all seats remaining unsold after the sale&#44; shall be fixed at the average of the entire pre&#45;emption&#44; paid at the sale.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Any member who is in arrears six months&#44; shall not be permitted to purchase a seat in the Synagogue until<lb/> said arrears are paid up&#44; and it shall be discretionary with the Board to deprive any person of his seats&#44; on his refusing<lb/> or neglecting to pay for the same punctually every month.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Seats can be purchased after the public sale by applying to the President.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The lease of all the seats shall expire at one time&#44; say twenty four months from the date of purchase.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Seats to be selected by the purchaser at the time of adjudication.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><emph rend="italics">By order of the board.</emph></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName>ALEX. ABRAMS</persName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(12)"><emph rend="italics">Secretary</emph></p>
				<p><placeName>NEW ORLEANS</placeName>&#44; <date><emph rend="italics">March</emph> 23&#44; 1857</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><date>5617</date>.</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>Dear <addressee>Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">As I intend to forward<lb/> you exclusively all news<lb/> of the Congregation I send you<lb/>  the enclosed as a beginning&#44;<lb/> after the <date>1st</date> I will supply<lb/> you with further matter</p>
				<p>Did I mention to you that</p>
